==English==

===Pronunciation===
* ''[[RP]]:'' {{IPA|/ˈwʌri/}}
* ''US:'' {{IPA|/ˈwɜːri/}}

===Noun===
'''worry'''
# A cause of [[anxiety]]; a source of [[unhappiness]].
# A strong [[feeling]] of anxiety.

====Derived terms====
*[[worrisome]]

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[huoli]] (1,2), [[harmi]] (1,2)
*French: [[souci]], [[angoisse]]
*Hungarian: [[aggodalom]]
*German: [[Sorge]]
*Italian: [[preoccupazione]]
*Polish: [[zmartwienie]] ''n''
*Romanian: [[teamă]]
*Spanish: [[preocupación]]
*Swedish: [[bekymmer]]
*[[Brasilian Portuguese]]: [[preocupação]]

===Verb===
'''to worry'''
# To be troubled by something.
# To be [[concern]]ed about, to [[care]].
# Disturb the [[peace of mind]] of; afflict with mental [[agitation]] or [[distress]].
# to stress or cause distress, as in "the hound worried the rabbit in its jaws"

